TITLE: Fetching OHLCV Data with CCXT in Python
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to fetch OHLCV data for all markets on an exchange using the `fetch_ohlcv` method in Python. It iterates through each market, adds a delay to respect rate limits, and then fetches the OHLCV data for a 1-day timeframe.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/wiki/Manual.md#_snippet_94

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import time
if exchange.has['fetchOHLCV']:
    for symbol in exchange.markets:
        time.sleep (exchange.rateLimit / 1000) # time.sleep wants seconds
        print (symbol, exchange.fetch_ohlcv (symbol, '1d')) # one day
```

