TITLE: Watching Order Book in Python
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to watch the order book using the `watch_order_book` method in Python within CCXT Pro. It continuously fetches and prints the top asks and bids of the order book for a given symbol. The code includes error handling to catch and log any exceptions, allowing for retries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/wiki/ccxt.pro.manual.md#_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
if exchange.has['watchOrderBook']:
    while True:
        try:
            orderbook = await exchange.watch_order_book(symbol, limit, params)
            print(exchange.iso8601(exchange.milliseconds()), symbol, orderbook['asks'][0], orderbook['bids'][0])
        except Exception as e:
            print(e)
            # stop the loop on exception or leave it commented to retry
            # raise e
```

