TITLE: Instantiating a CCXT Pro Exchange (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to instantiate a CCXT Pro exchange instance in JavaScript, specifically a Binance exchange. It sets the `newUpdates` option to `false`, disabling the exclusive new updates mode and utilizing the sliding cache. This demonstrates how to create an exchange object that can be used to interact with the Binance API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/wiki/ccxt.pro.manual.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const ccxt = require ('ccxt').pro
const exchange = new ccxtpro.binance ({ newUpdates: false })
```

