TITLE: Creating Stop-Loss and Take-Profit Orders
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create orders with stop-loss and take-profit parameters. Shows implementation in multiple languages with support for both market and limit order types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/doc/manual.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_121

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const params = {
    'stopLoss': {
        'type': 'limit', // or 'market'
        'price': 100.33,
        'triggerPrice': 101.25,
    },
    'takeProfit': {
        'type': 'market',
        'triggerPrice': 150.75,
    }
}
const order = await exchange.createOrder (symbol, type, side, amount, price, params)
```

LANGUAGE: Python
CODE:
```
symbol = 'ETH/BTC'
type = 'limit'  # or 'market'
side = 'buy'
amount = 123.45  # your amount
price = 115.321  # your price
