TITLE: Implementing createOrder Method in JavaScript for CCXT
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of the createOrder method that places new trade orders on the exchange. It prepares parameters, submits the order to the API, and returns a standardized order object with ID, symbol, and status information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/ts/src/static_dependencies/ethers/utils/test.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async createOrder (symbol, type, side, amount, price = undefined, params = {}) {
    await this.loadMarkets ();
    const market = this.market (symbol);
    // construct request
    const request = {
        'symbol': market['id'],
        'side': side,
        'type': type,
        'amount': amount,
    };
    if (type !== 'market') {
        request['price'] = price;
    }
    // make a specific API call
    const response = await this.privatePostEndpointPath (this.extend (request, params));
    // response is a single order
    // response = {
    //     'id': '1234567890',
    //     'symbol': 'BTC/USD',
    //     'side': 'buy',
    //     'type': 'limit',
    //     'amount': 1.2345,
    //     'price': 1234.5,
    //     'timestamp': 1234567890,
    //     'status': 'open',
    //     ...
    // }
    // parse that order and return a unified order structure
    return this.parseOrder (response, market);
}
```

