TITLE: Calculating Liquidation Price in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to calculate the liquidation price for long and short positions. The formulas are provided for both regular and inverse contracts, using the current price, contract size, and maintenance margin.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/wiki/Manual.md#_snippet_283

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// if long
(liquidationPrice - price) * contracts = maintenanceMargin

// if short
(price - liquidationPrice) * contracts = maintenanceMargin
// if inverse long
(1/liquidationPrice - 1/price) * contracts = maintenanceMargin

// if inverse short
(1/price - 1/liquidationPrice) * contracts = maintenanceMargin
```

