TITLE: Configuring Custom Nonce in Python
DESCRIPTION: Multiple approaches for implementing custom nonce functionality in Python, including direct nonce assignment, subclassing exchange classes, and using lambda functions for milliseconds-based nonce.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/doc/manual.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_100

LANGUAGE: Python
CODE:
```
# Python

# 1: the shortest
coinbasepro = ccxt.coinbasepro({'nonce': ccxt.Exchange.milliseconds})

# 2: custom nonce
class MyKraken(ccxt.kraken):
    n = 1
    def nonce(self):
        return self.n += 1

# 3: milliseconds nonce
class MyBitfinex(ccxt.bitfinex):
    def nonce(self):
        return self.milliseconds()

# 4: milliseconds nonce inline
hitbtc = ccxt.hitbtc({
    'nonce': lambda: int(time.time() * 1000)
})

# 5: milliseconds nonce
acx = ccxt.acx({'nonce': lambda: ccxt.Exchange.milliseconds()})
```

