TITLE: Configuring Custom Nonce in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Examples of custom nonce implementation in PHP through class extension, showing both incremental integer nonce and milliseconds-based nonce approaches.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/doc/manual.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_101

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
// PHP

// 1: custom nonce value
class MyOKCoinUSD extends \ccxt\okcoinusd {
    public function __construct ($options = array ()) {
        parent::__construct (array_merge (array ('i' => 1), $options));
    }
    public function nonce () {
        return $this->i++;
    }
}

// 2: milliseconds nonce
class MyZaif extends \ccxt\zaif {
    public function __construct ($options = array ()) {
        parent::__construct (array_merge (array ('i' => 1), $options));
    }
    public function nonce () {
        return $this->milliseconds ();
    }
}
```

