TITLE: Watching OHLCV Data with WebSocket in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Continuously watches for OHLCV (candlestick) data updates using the exchange's WebSocket API. Prints the received candles as JSON and handles exceptions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/doc/ccxt.pro.manual.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
if ($exchange->has['watchOHLCV']) {
    $exchange::execute_and_run(function() use ($exchange, $symbol, $timeframe, $since, $limit, $params) {
        while (true) {
            try {
                $candles = yield $exchange->watch_ohlcv($symbol, $timeframe, $since, $limit, $params);
                echo date('c'), ' ', $symbol, ' ', $timeframe, ' ', json_encode($candles), "\n";
            } catch (Exception $e) {
                echo get_class($e), ' ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
            }
        }
    });
}
```

