TITLE: Memory Leak Example with Native Promise.race
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the typical memory leak scenario that occurs when using Promise.race with long-lived promises, which the Unpromise library aims to solve.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/ts/src/static_dependencies/watchable/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const interruptPromise = new Promise((resolve) => {
  process.once("SIGINT", () => resolve("interrupted"));
});

async function run() {
  let count = 0;
  for (; ; count++) {
    const taskPromise = new Promise((resolve) => {
      // an imaginary task
      setImmediate(() => resolve("task_result"));
    });
    const result = await Promise.race([taskPromise, interruptPromise]);
    if (result === "interrupted") {
      break;
    }
    console.log(`Completed ${count} tasks`);
  }
  console.log(`Interrupted by user`);
}

run();
```

