TITLE: Fetching Orders with PageNumber-Based Pagination in CCXT
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates fetching orders using page number-based pagination in Python. It uses a 'cursor' variable and updates it based on the exchange's response headers to retrieve the next page of results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/wiki/Manual.md#_snippet_73

LANGUAGE: Python
CODE:
```
if exchange.has['fetchOrders']:
    cursor = 0  # exchange-specific type and value
    all_orders = []
    while True:
        symbol = None  # change for your symbol
        since = None
        limit = 20  # change for your limit
        params = {
            'cursor': cursor,  # exchange-specific non-unified parameter name
        }
        orders = await exchange.fetch_orders(symbol, since, limit, params)
        if len(orders):
            # not thread-safu and exchange-specific !
            cursor = exchange.last_response_headers['CB-AFTER']
            all_orders += orders
        else:
            break
```

