TITLE: Overriding parse_ohlcv in Python to get raw response
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to override the `parse_ohlcv` function in Python to access the raw OHLCV response from the exchange. It appends the raw OHLCV data to the end of the parsed result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/blob/master/wiki/Manual.md#_snippet_97

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
# add raw member at last position in list
async def test():
    ex = ccxt.async_support.coinbase()
    prase_ohlcv_original = ex.parse_ohlcv
    def prase_ohlcv_custom(ohlcv, market):
        res = prase_ohlcv_original(ohlcv, market)
        res.append(ohlcv)
        return res
    ex.parse_ohlcv = prase_ohlcv_custom
    result = await ex.fetch_ohlcv('BTC/USDT', '1m')
    print (result[0])

asyncio.run(test())
```

